reviewText: Product received for free\n\nA spiritual successor to There's Poop In My Soup, this game is yet another silly game involving poop humor. While the gameplay of Soup was very simple, easy, and you take it at your own pace, this game is much faster, and actually much for difficult (I actually couldn't finish it). Most of the game involves you eating food by hitting the corresponding key quickly enough, which honestly wasn't that fun of a mechanic because there's such a huge margin for error. This kind of control would actually work really well on a mobile version of this game though, and I would hope that this and Soup get ported to mobile eventually. After creating" the poop
date: then you fling it at a group of partygoers. Pretty simple
recommended: and there's actually less to do in this than Soup (Soup had a list of goals
hoursPlayed: this one is to just get a high score). This and Soup are easily just joke games and YouTuber bait
voteText: but at the base level it's a fun game to kill 20 minutes with...maybe even get a laugh or two as you smack some poor fellow in the face with a turd.\n\nIt should be noted that most people won't realize that you can add your own music to this game. So instead of listening to the royalty free tracks (I actually noticed a song with a "PremiumBeat.com" in the background
helpfulPercent: even made a joke about it
votesHelpful: saying that I thought it said "PremiumMeat.com")
votesTotal: you can shove in your own tracks. Obviously you won't seen that on YouTube
votesFunny: as you'll get copyright problems.\n\nIs this obviously a cash-in on the success of Soup? Totally. Does that necessarily make this game bad? No. Would I recommend for you to buy it? Sure
